text:
Title: Hostname not resolving due to incorrect DNS server
Symptoms: Internal application not accessible, Ping to hostname fails
Errors: Ping request could not find host, DNS request timed out
Root cause: Client system configured with public DNS instead of internal DNS resolver
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check configured DNS servers using ipconfig /all
2. Update DNS server to internal DNS IP provided by network team
3. Flush DNS cache using ipconfig /flushdns

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname using nslookup
2. Verify resolved IP matches expected internal service IP
3. Confirm application loads successfully

Tools: ipconfig, nslookup

Title: DNS resolution fails due to stale local DNS cache
Symptoms: Hostname resolves to outdated IP address, Application intermittently unreachable
Errors: Connection timed out
Root cause: Stale DNS record cached locally on the client machine
Severity: P3
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Flush DNS cache using ipconfig /flushdns
2. Restart network interface if issue persists

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname using nslookup
2. Confirm correct and updated IP address is returned

Tools: ipconfig, nslookup

Title: NXDOMAIN error due to missing DNS record
Symptoms: Hostname does not resolve, Service completely unavailable
Errors: NXDOMAIN
Root cause: Required DNS record not present in authoritative DNS zone
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify DNS record existence using nslookup
2. Create missing DNS record in authoritative DNS server

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname using nslookup
2. Confirm service is reachable

Tools: nslookup

Title: DNS queries timing out due to unreachable DNS server
Symptoms: All hostname resolutions failing, Slow network operations
Errors: DNS request timed out
Root cause: Configured DNS server unreachable due to network connectivity issue
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Ping configured DNS server to verify connectivity
2. Update DNS server configuration to reachable secondary DNS server

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname using nslookup
2. Confirm DNS queries complete without timeout

Tools: ping, nslookup

Title: Incorrect DNS record pointing to wrong IP address
Symptoms: Application loads incorrect service, Unexpected application behavior
Errors: Connection established to wrong host
Root cause: DNS A record incorrectly configured with outdated IP address
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify current DNS record using nslookup
2. Update DNS record to correct IP address in DNS server

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname using nslookup
2. Verify returned IP matches intended service

Tools: nslookup

Title: Split DNS issue between internal and external networks
Symptoms: Hostname resolves internally but fails externally, Users outside network unable to access service
Errors: DNS request timed out
Root cause: DNS records configured only in internal DNS zone and missing in external DNS
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify DNS resolution from internal and external networks
2. Add required DNS record to external DNS zone

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname from external network using nslookup
2. Confirm service is accessible externally

Tools: nslookup

Title: DNS resolution slow due to misconfigured DNS forwarders
Symptoms: Delayed hostname resolution, Noticeable application startup delays
Errors: DNS response delayed
Root cause: DNS forwarders configured to unreachable or slow upstream servers
Severity: P3
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review DNS forwarder configuration
2. Update forwarders to reachable and recommended DNS servers

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname using nslookup
2. Confirm DNS response time is acceptable

Tools: nslookup

Title: Local hosts file overriding DNS resolution
Symptoms: Hostname resolves to unexpected IP, Issue persists despite DNS record correction
Errors: Incorrect IP address returned
Root cause: Hostname entry present in local hosts file overriding DNS resolution
Severity: P3
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check local hosts file for hostname entry
2. Remove or correct incorrect hosts file entry
3. Flush DNS cache using ipconfig /flushdns

Validation steps:
1. Resolve hostname using nslookup
2. Confirm correct IP address is returned

Tools: ipconfig, nslookup

Title: Firewall blocking internal application traffic
Symptoms: Application not accessible, Connection times out
Errors: Request timed out
Root cause: Firewall rule missing to allow application traffic
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Identify source and destination IPs and ports
2. Create firewall rule to allow required traffic
3. Apply and commit firewall configuration

Validation steps:
1. Access application successfully
2. Verify traffic allowed in firewall logs

Tools: firewall-console, ping

Title: Firewall rule order causing traffic drop
Symptoms: Traffic blocked despite allow rule present
Errors: Denied by policy
Root cause: Allow rule placed below a deny rule
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review firewall rule order
2. Move allow rule above deny rule
3. Apply configuration changes

Validation steps:
1. Confirm traffic is permitted

Tools: firewall-console

Title: Firewall NAT misconfiguration
Symptoms: External users cannot reach internal service
Errors: Connection failed
Root cause: Incorrect NAT rule mapping public IP to internal server
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify NAT configuration
2. Correct destination NAT rule
3. Commit firewall changes

Validation steps:
1. Access service from external network

Tools: firewall-console

Title: Firewall blocking outbound internet access
Symptoms: Users cannot access internet
Errors: Connection timed out
Root cause: Outbound firewall rule missing or misconfigured
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review outbound firewall rules
2. Add or correct outbound allow rule
3. Apply firewall configuration

Validation steps:
1. Access external website

Tools: firewall-console

Title: Firewall IPS blocking legitimate traffic
Symptoms: Intermittent application failures
Errors: Connection reset
Root cause: Intrusion Prevention System falsely blocking traffic
Severity: P3
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review IPS logs
2. Create IPS exception for application traffic
3. Apply updated IPS policy

Validation steps:
1. Monitor application stability

Tools: firewall-console

Title: Firewall high CPU causing packet drops
Symptoms: Slow network performance, Intermittent packet loss
Errors: Packet dropped
Root cause: Firewall under high load due to excessive traffic
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check firewall CPU and memory usage
2. Optimize firewall rules
3. Scale firewall resources if required

Validation steps:
1. Verify CPU usage normalized
2. Confirm traffic stability

Tools: firewall-console

Title: Firewall rule expired or disabled
Symptoms: Previously working service suddenly unavailable
Errors: Connection refused
Root cause: Firewall rule expired or manually disabled
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review firewall rule status
2. Re-enable or recreate firewall rule
3. Commit configuration

Validation steps:
1. Access service successfully

Tools: firewall-console

Title: Firewall blocking traffic due to incorrect security zone
Symptoms: Traffic blocked between internal networks
Errors: Denied by zone policy
Root cause: Source or destination assigned to wrong security zone
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify security zone assignments
2. Correct zone mapping
3. Apply firewall configuration

Validation steps:
1. Confirm inter-zone traffic allowed

Tools: firewall-console

Title: Load balancer VIP not responding
Symptoms: Application inaccessible, VIP does not respond to ping or HTTP
Errors: Connection timed out
Root cause: Load balancer service down or VIP disabled
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check load balancer service status
2. Verify VIP configuration
3. Restart load balancer service if required

Validation steps:
1. Access application via VIP

Tools: lb-console, ping

Title: Backend servers marked down
Symptoms: Application intermittently unavailable
Errors: No available backend servers
Root cause: Health check failing on backend servers
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check health check configuration
2. Verify backend server health
3. Fix application or port issues on backend

Validation steps:
1. Confirm backend servers marked up

Tools: lb-console

Title: Incorrect load balancing algorithm causing uneven traffic
Symptoms: One backend overloaded, Other backends idle
Errors: Performance degradation
Root cause: Load balancing algorithm misconfigured
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review load balancing algorithm
2. Update algorithm to round-robin or least-connections
3. Apply configuration changes

Validation steps:
1. Verify traffic distributed evenly

Tools: lb-console

Title: SSL certificate expired on load balancer
Symptoms: Browser security warnings, HTTPS access fails
Errors: SSL certificate expired
Root cause: Expired SSL certificate on load balancer
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Install renewed SSL certificate
2. Bind certificate to VIP
3. Reload SSL configuration

Validation steps:
1. Access HTTPS site without warnings

Tools: lb-console

Title: Persistence misconfiguration breaking user sessions
Symptoms: Users logged out frequently, Session data lost
Errors: Session not found
Root cause: Session persistence not configured correctly
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review persistence settings
2. Enable cookie-based or source-IP persistence
3. Apply changes

Validation steps:
1. Verify session stability

Tools: lb-console

Title: Load balancer SNAT issue causing backend connectivity failure
Symptoms: Backend servers cannot respond to clients
Errors: Connection reset
Root cause: SNAT disabled or misconfigured
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review SNAT configuration
2. Enable SNAT for backend traffic
3. Apply configuration changes

Validation steps:
1. Confirm backend responses reach clients

Tools: lb-console

Title: Load balancer high CPU usage
Symptoms: Slow application response, Intermittent connection failures
Errors: Packet drops
Root cause: Load balancer overloaded due to traffic spike
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check CPU and memory usage
2. Optimize configuration
3. Scale load balancer resources

Validation steps:
1. Verify performance stabilizes

Tools: lb-console

Title: Health monitor using incorrect port
Symptoms: Backends marked down despite being healthy
Errors: Health check failed
Root cause: Health monitor configured with wrong port or protocol
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review health monitor configuration
2. Correct port and protocol
3. Apply changes

Validation steps:
1. Confirm backends marked up

Tools: lb-console

Title: Users cannot access internet through proxy
Symptoms: Websites do not load, All browser traffic blocked
Errors: Connection timed out
Root cause: Proxy service down or unreachable
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check proxy server status
2. Restart proxy service if down
3. Verify network connectivity to proxy

Validation steps:
1. Access external website successfully

Tools: proxy-console, ping

Title: Proxy authentication failure
Symptoms: Browser prompts repeatedly for credentials
Errors: 407 Proxy Authentication Required
Root cause: Invalid user credentials or authentication service issue
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify user credentials
2. Check proxy authentication backend
3. Clear cached browser credentials

Validation steps:
1. Authenticate successfully through proxy

Tools: browser

Title: Proxy PAC file misconfiguration
Symptoms: Some websites accessible, others not, Inconsistent browsing behavior
Errors: Proxy configuration error
Root cause: Incorrect PAC file logic or unreachable PAC URL
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify PAC file URL
2. Correct PAC file rules
3. Force browser to reload PAC file

Validation steps:
1. Confirm consistent website access

Tools: browser

Title: SSL inspection blocking secure websites
Symptoms: HTTPS websites fail to load, Security warnings in browser
Errors: SSL certificate error
Root cause: Proxy SSL inspection enabled without trusted certificate on client
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Install proxy CA certificate on client
2. Verify SSL inspection policy
3. Test HTTPS access

Validation steps:
1. Access HTTPS website without warnings

Tools: browser

Title: Proxy bypass rule missing for internal services
Symptoms: Internal applications fail when proxy is enabled
Errors: Connection failed
Root cause: Internal domains not excluded from proxy bypass list
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review proxy bypass configuration
2. Add internal domains to bypass list
3. Apply proxy configuration

Validation steps:
1. Access internal application successfully

Tools: proxy-console

Title: Proxy performance degradation
Symptoms: Slow internet access, High latency when browsing
Errors: Slow response time
Root cause: Proxy overloaded due to high traffic
Severity: P3
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check proxy CPU and memory usage
2. Optimize proxy policies
3. Scale proxy resources if required

Validation steps:
1. Confirm browsing performance improved

Tools: proxy-console

Title: Proxy blocking file downloads
Symptoms: File downloads fail
Errors: Download blocked by policy
Root cause: Proxy content filtering policy blocking file type
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review content filtering rules
2. Allow required file type
3. Apply proxy policy changes

Validation steps:
1. Download file successfully

Tools: proxy-console

Title: Proxy configuration not applied to clients
Symptoms: Some users bypass proxy unintentionally
Errors: Direct internet access
Root cause: Proxy settings not pushed via GPO or device management
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify proxy deployment mechanism
2. Reapply proxy configuration
3. Restart affected clients

Validation steps:
1. Confirm traffic flows through proxy

Tools: proxy-console

Title: VPN connected but internal resources not accessible
Symptoms: VPN tunnel established, Cannot access internal servers
Errors: Request timed out
Root cause: Internal routes not pushed to VPN client
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify routes configured on VPN server
2. Update VPN server to push internal network routes
3. Reconnect VPN client

Validation steps:
1. Ping internal server
2. Confirm traffic flows through VPN tunnel

Tools: ping, tracert

Title: VPN authentication failure
Symptoms: VPN connection fails during login
Errors: Authentication failed
Root cause: Invalid user credentials or expired VPN certificate
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify user credentials
2. Check VPN certificate validity
3. Reset VPN credentials if required

Validation steps:
1. Reconnect VPN successfully

Tools: vpn-client

Title: VPN tunnel disconnects intermittently
Symptoms: VPN connection drops randomly
Errors: Connection reset by peer
Root cause: Unstable network connection or VPN keepalive misconfiguration
Severity: P3
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check client network stability
2. Adjust VPN keepalive settings
3. Reconnect VPN client

Validation steps:
1. Monitor VPN connection stability

Tools: ping

Title: VPN connected but DNS resolution fails
Symptoms: Cannot resolve internal hostnames over VPN
Errors: DNS request timed out
Root cause: DNS servers not pushed to VPN client
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Verify DNS server settings on VPN server
2. Configure VPN to push internal DNS servers
3. Reconnect VPN client

Validation steps:
1. Resolve internal hostname using nslookup

Tools: nslookup

Title: Split tunneling misconfiguration blocks internal access
Symptoms: Some internal services unreachable over VPN
Errors: Request timed out
Root cause: Split tunneling enabled without required internal routes
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Review split tunneling configuration
2. Add missing internal routes or disable split tunneling
3. Reconnect VPN client

Validation steps:
1. Access previously unreachable internal service

Tools: tracert

Title: VPN traffic fails due to MTU mismatch
Symptoms: VPN connects but some applications fail, Large packets dropped
Errors: Packet fragmentation needed
Root cause: MTU size mismatch between VPN client and server
Severity: P3
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Reduce MTU size on VPN client
2. Apply recommended MTU settings on VPN server
3. Reconnect VPN client

Validation steps:
1. Test application functionality over VPN

Tools: ping

Title: VPN connected but traffic routes outside tunnel
Symptoms: Internet traffic bypasses VPN, Internal services unreachable
Errors: Incorrect routing table
Root cause: Default route not set to VPN interface
Severity: P2
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Check routing table on VPN client
2. Update VPN configuration to route traffic via tunnel
3. Reconnect VPN client

Validation steps:
1. Verify routing table
2. Access internal service successfully

Tools: route

Title: VPN server unreachable
Symptoms: VPN connection cannot be established
Errors: Unable to reach VPN server
Root cause: VPN server down or network path blocked
Severity: P1
Environment: prod

Resolution steps:
1. Ping VPN server to verify reachability
2. Check firewall rules allowing VPN traffic
3. Restart VPN service if required

Validation steps:
1. Connect to VPN successfully

Tools: ping
